 CROSS-SECTION EVALUATION PROCEDURE                               5428 1451
                                                                  5428 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                5428 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               5428 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             5428 1451
                                                                  5428 1451
 This code integrates into a single system a number               5428 1451
 of important modules and features:                               5428 1451
                                                                  5428 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 5428 1451
   coupled-channels code ECIS06 by J. Raynal                      5428 1451
 - Soft-rotator deformed Optical Model including                  5428 1451
   coupled-channels code OPTMAN by E.Soukhovitskii                5428 1451
   and coworkers                                                  5428 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    5428 1451
   width fluctuation correction, and the                          5428 1451
   optical model for fission with partial damping                 5428 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                5428 1451
   TRISTAN by H.Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                       5428 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      5428 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 5428 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                5428 1451
 - Hybrid Monte Carlo preequilibrium model(M.Blann)               5428 1451
   (code DDHMS by M.Chadwick, mod. by B.V.Carlson)                5428 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   5428 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                5428 1451
   discrete transitions                                           5428 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL library [RIPL]                5428 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                5428 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               5428 1451
   and gamma strength functions based on the RIPL                 5428 1451
   library [RIPL]                                                 5428 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              5428 1451
   EXFOR library                                                  5428 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A.Trkov)                     5428 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 5428 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                5428 1451
   PrePro codes by D. Cullen                                      5428 1451
 - ENDF checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                   5428 1451
 - Highly automated fitting of optical model                      5428 1451
   parameters (by B.V. Carlson)                                   5428 1451
 - KALMAN code for fitting experimental data and                  5428 1451
 - generating covariances                                         5428 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               5428 1451
